docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Aug. 9. -- Federal appointments in New York City are being held up until after the selection of the city ticket, it became known today. Although the Tammany leaders have strongly urged the President to fill the jobs in advance of that time, he has refused and has not even intimated that they will be recognized in the few jobs not yet filled in Manhattan.

docs.lead_paragraph: ONCE upon a time there flourished what was known as the impressionistic school of writers, although latterly not so much has been heard of them, so many other schools having clamored for a hearing. Whether there can be "impressionism" in writing, many have questioned, while granting that in the field of painting there can be no questioning the designation.

docs.lead_paragraph: President Roosevelt in his foreign policy is aiming at "a new ideal in the relations between States" and "a Foreign Service not solely concerned with the development of our own interests," Alexander W. Weddell, newly appointed Ambassador to Argentina, said yesterday.
